    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Form of sodium chloride, with small amounts of magnesium chloride, magnesium sulfate, and calcium sulfate, that is obtained from the evaporation of salt water; often comprising larger crystals than table salt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
